main event: Several persons reported seeing an unusual light or object in the sky near Humboldt, Saskatchewan, Canada on the evening of December 6, 1961.
interesting points: The object was first sighted at approximately 7:30 p.m. and was observed for about 30 minutes., The object was described as a bright light, possibly rotating or spinning., Some witnesses reported the object seemed to increase in size and then decrease during the observation., The object was seen maneuvering in the sky before disappearing from view., No photographs or physical evidence was obtained, and the Air Force is investigating the reports.
sighted object: bright light possibly rotating in the sky
witness description: Civilian, details of other witnesses are limited
